</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Mutuals are a feature that allows the user to view mutual friends or groups of other users.
</div> 

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
There are two ways to see mutuals, in the Quick Menu or the Main Menu with a button "Show X Mutuals". In the Quick Menu, the button can be found on top of user actions. In the Main Menu, the button will be found on the top right, next to the report button.
</div> 

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
If you wish to prevent other users from seeing your mutual friends and groups or appearing as so for others, you can turn off "Show Mutual Connections" in the '''Comfort & Safety''' section of your settings in the Main Menu. Doing so will change the text of the button from "Show X Mutuals" to "No Known Mutuals". Additionally, your user icon will be hidden, and your username will appear as "Hidden Mutual" when you appear in the mutuals in one of your friends.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Discord Friends==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Seen in the Social tab under "All Friends", this feature allows you to see your Discord friends with their current status and to perform different actions. Friends with a Discord account linked will have a Discord icon displayed on their profile
</div> 

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
If your friend has linked their Discord account to their VRChat account, you will be able to invite them to join your instance through Discord. Otherwise, you will be able to invite them to create a VRChat account. You or your friends may prevent your VRChat account from being shown in the Discord section by turning off the "Allow Discord Friends" setting in the '''Comfort & Safety''' section of the settings.
</div>

